Question
========
A researcher performs a regression analysis using SPSS and receives the
following ANOVA table:  
  
<img src="1644915328114.png" class="fr-fic fr-dii tvcss_2"
alt="1644915328114" />  
  
How much variance of Y is explained by this regression model?

Answerlist
----------
* 4.2%
* 4.8%
* 5.1%
* This can not be calculated on the basis of the above output.

Solution
========





You can calculate the R<sup>2</sup> by (total sum of squares -residual)
/ total sum of squares=(2564,601-2433,288)/ 2564,601=
131,313/2564,601=0,051  
Thus 5,1 %
